<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>Michael Jay Lissner</title><link href="http://michaeljaylissner.com/" rel="alternate"></link><link href="http://michaeljaylissner.com/feeds/tag/software" rel="self"></link><id>http://michaeljaylissner.com/</id><updated>2010-01-12T16:28:02-08:00</updated><entry><title>2010 Donations</title><link href="http://michaeljaylissner.com/posts/2010/01/12/2010-donations/" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2010-01-12T16:28:02-08:00</updated><author><name>Michael Lissner</name></author><id>tag:michaeljaylissner.com,2010-01-12:posts/2010/01/12/2010-donations/</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Every year, a handful of organizations reach out to me to give them my money. I'm never sure how much I've given them, when the last time was, etc, so I'm always convinced some of them are tricking me into donating more than I would otherwise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Well, this shall happen no more. I'm starting a new scheme this year in which on January 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt; of each year, I donate to all the organizations that make the cut. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here are this year's results, including amount donated and links to their donation page. Please let me know if I'm making any grave mistakes:
